9
00:00:12,920 --> 00:00:14,130
How we doing, Pops?

10
00:00:14,130 --> 00:00:16,200
You know, like I got a week to figure out

11
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:18,040
the hell I'm gonna do with my days.

12
00:00:18,330 --> 00:00:21,180
30 years, and my only hobby was bitching about my job.

13
00:00:21,760 --> 00:00:23,160
Ah, that's the cop way.

14
00:00:23,780 --> 00:00:25,850
- You'll figure it out. - Yeah.

15
00:00:26,740 --> 00:00:27,660
Gentlemen.

16
00:00:27,920 --> 00:00:29,470
- Bob! - Rizzy!

17
00:00:29,470 --> 00:00:31,380
- Old man. - Hey, Bob.

18
00:00:31,570 --> 00:00:32,910
You remember my boy, Adam.

19
00:00:32,910 --> 00:00:34,670
With scruff on his face, I don't.

20
00:00:34,670 --> 00:00:35,560
Hey, Duff.

21
00:00:35,660 --> 00:00:37,680
We just wanted to stop by, see how you usually do it.

22
00:00:37,680 --> 00:00:39,950
Yeah, we got these things down pretty good, I think.

23
00:00:39,950 --> 00:00:41,480
Figure you don't need the whole place, right?

24
00:00:41,480 --> 00:00:43,580
No, no. 15, 20 max.

25
00:00:43,580 --> 00:00:46,100
Well, we'll get that area closed off,

26
00:00:46,100 --> 00:00:48,260
set aside for you, put out some snacks.

27
00:00:48,260 --> 00:00:49,410
Won't be too complicated.

28
00:00:49,410 --> 00:00:51,300
Usually take a little deposit.

29
00:00:52,010 --> 00:00:53,190
200 maybe?

30
00:00:53,310 --> 00:00:56,140
- Seems fair. - Uh, yeah, yeah, hang on.

31
00:00:57,980 --> 00:00:58,910
Hang on.

32
00:01:00,790 --> 00:01:02,220
Dad, I got it.

33
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:04,900
Yeah?

34
00:01:05,330 --> 00:01:06,790
You don't pay for your own retirement party.

35
00:01:06,790 --> 00:01:07,630
Come on.

36
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:08,950
Bob Ruzek.

37
00:01:09,210 --> 00:01:10,920
Finally putting you out to pasture.

38
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:13,810
Well, better than being taken behind the barn and shot, I guess.

39
00:01:14,890 --> 00:01:16,070
That's right.

40
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:21,460
What does it say about the Chicago Police Department

41
00:01:21,460 --> 00:01:24,110
that you turkeys serve up the best coffee in the building?

42
00:01:24,110 --> 00:01:25,660
Nothing good, Sarge.

43
00:01:26,110 --> 00:01:28,690
I saw the flyer downstairs about Disco Bob's party.

44
00:01:28,690 --> 00:01:31,380
Yeah, this weekend. No obligation.

45
00:01:31,420 --> 00:01:34,100
Are you nuts? I don't go to those things.

46
00:01:34,620 --> 00:01:37,940
Years ago, when we were babies working at the 13th,

47
00:01:37,940 --> 00:01:40,460
your dad would show up for his shift

48
00:01:40,490 --> 00:01:43,370
reciting your stats from your game the night before.

49
00:01:43,550 --> 00:01:45,610
"Adam went three for four last night

50
00:01:45,610 --> 00:01:47,650
with a double and two RBIs."

51
00:01:47,650 --> 00:01:49,260
Well, we should definitely keep doing that.

52
00:01:49,270 --> 00:01:50,950
Adam went three for four last night

53
00:01:50,950 --> 00:01:52,110
with a hoagie and two beers.

54
00:01:52,110 --> 00:01:53,490
And a sacrifice pickle.

55
00:01:53,490 --> 00:01:54,270
Heyo.

56
00:01:54,750 --> 00:01:56,220
Something for your old man.

57
00:01:57,220 --> 00:01:58,780
Thanks, boss. You didn't have to do that.

58
00:01:58,780 --> 00:02:00,790
I know you had your issues with him over the years.

59
00:02:00,790 --> 00:02:02,900
30 years of service to the city of Chicago

60
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:05,120
is 30 years of service-- end of story.

61
00:02:05,330 --> 00:02:06,200
Appreciate it.

62
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:13,040
What are you hungry for for dinner?

63
00:02:13,580 --> 00:02:15,220
Let's go to that place on Clybourn.

64
00:02:15,220 --> 00:02:17,640
What do you call it? Platonic Pizza?

65
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:18,880
Platonic Pie.

66
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:20,570
Oh, 'cause that's so much snappier.

67
00:02:20,710 --> 00:02:21,870
It's a skillset.

68
00:02:23,130 --> 00:02:24,880
Swing by my dad's house quick.

69
00:02:28,750 --> 00:02:29,550
All right.

70
00:02:29,650 --> 00:02:30,780
I'll just run this inside,

71
00:02:30,780 --> 00:02:32,310
and then we'll go pick up Makayla.

72
00:02:32,310 --> 00:02:33,090
Okay?

73
00:02:34,610 --> 00:02:35,690
Actually, you know what?

74
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:37,500
Why don't you come in, see the old man?

75
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:39,120
He'd be happy to see your face.

76
00:02:39,290 --> 00:02:40,070
Come on.

77
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:42,960
- You sure? - Yeah, come on.

78
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:44,460
- Sure, sure? - Yeah.

79
00:02:47,490 --> 00:02:49,000
Have you told him about...

80
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,190
All the times you broke my heart?

81
00:02:50,190 --> 00:02:51,690
No. You're good.

82
00:02:52,020 --> 00:02:53,530
Are you protecting me from his wrath?

83
00:02:53,530 --> 00:02:55,820
No, I just figured if he was ever forced to make a choice,

84
00:02:55,820 --> 00:02:56,680
he'd pick you over me.

85
00:02:56,690 --> 00:02:58,440
I mean, that's the choice I would make.

86
00:02:59,210 --> 00:03:01,040
Pops, I hope you're decent.

87
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:02,400
Coming in with the girl.

88
00:03:07,230 --> 00:03:08,050
Dad?

89
00:03:11,940 --> 00:03:12,910
Hey, Dad?

90
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:14,590
Dad?

91
00:03:16,980 --> 00:03:17,770
Bob?

92
00:03:21,230 --> 00:03:22,070
Adam.

93
00:03:29,140 --> 00:03:30,440
All right. I'm gonna call him.

94
00:03:30,580 --> 00:03:31,340
Yeah.

95
00:03:34,100 --> 00:03:35,190
All right. It's ringing.

96
00:03:35,290 --> 00:03:36,630
What the hell is this?

97
00:03:38,990 --> 00:03:39,760
Dad?

99
00:03:58,830 --> 00:04:00,610
- More blood down here. - Yeah...

100
00:04:00,710 --> 00:04:01,560
Dad!

101
00:04:04,580 --> 00:04:06,140
That blood is fresh, Adam.

102
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:07,290
You got anything?

103
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:08,600
Uh, sort of.

104
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:09,630
I spoke to a neighbor.

105
00:04:09,630 --> 00:04:12,120
She said she saw two men pull up to the back of the house.

106
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:14,520
White, possibly Hispanic. They entered.

107
00:04:14,580 --> 00:04:16,360
Then they left about 20 minutes ago.

108
00:04:17,650 --> 00:04:19,140
It's a start. Call it in.

109
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:24,330
What?

110
00:04:24,860 --> 00:04:26,580
It's just, Kim, my dad, you know,

111
00:04:26,580 --> 00:04:29,250
he's made some pretty crappy choices over the years.

112
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:30,610
I don't know what happened in here,

113
00:04:30,610 --> 00:04:33,290
but there's a decent chance it was self-inflicted.

114
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:36,130
Maybe.

115
00:04:36,140 --> 00:04:38,960
But you gotta call it in.

116
00:04:42,550 --> 00:04:44,010
5021I
5021 Ida.

117
00:04:44,020 --> 00:04:45,210
Go ahead, Ida.

118
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:46,420
I need you to roll a crime lab

119
00:04:46,420 --> 00:04:48,390
to 221 North Oleander.

120
00:04:48,390 --> 00:04:51,170
Possible home invasion, possible kidnapping.

121
00:04:51,180 --> 00:04:53,290
Copy that. Crime lab en route.

123
00:05:03,420 --> 00:05:05,290
What up, dog? You good?

124
00:05:05,740 --> 00:05:06,780
I've been better.

125
00:05:07,190 --> 00:05:08,170
I don't know what happened there, boys,

126
00:05:08,170 --> 00:05:09,880
but it wasn't good, whatever it was.

127
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:11,370
Well, you know, whatever it is, we gonna figure it out.

128
00:05:11,370 --> 00:05:12,300
We got you.

129
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,320
Appreciate it, fellas.

130
00:05:15,530 --> 00:05:17,290
I told you to get that van out of here.

131
00:05:17,290 --> 00:05:18,350
Copy, Sergeant.

132
00:05:18,350 --> 00:05:19,900
All right. Everybody, listen to me.

133
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:22,930
The last thing Bob Ruzek needs

134
00:05:22,940 --> 00:05:24,410
is his face on the evening news.

135
00:05:24,420 --> 00:05:25,950
That's how people get hurt.

136
00:05:25,950 --> 00:05:26,930
Send patrol away.

137
00:05:26,930 --> 00:05:28,950
We're working this as a 99 Confidential.

138
00:05:28,950 --> 00:05:30,800
Only OCD in the loop.

139
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:33,130
But that means this is all on us.

140
00:05:34,350 --> 00:05:35,580
All right? Where are we?

141
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:37,420
Okay. We got a struggle inside the house.

142
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:38,220
There's blood in the kitchen

143
00:05:38,230 --> 00:05:39,520
which leads to the backdoor.

144
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:41,180
Pretty clear my father left in a hurry

145
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:42,580
and it wasn't his idea to do so.

146
00:05:42,580 --> 00:05:45,300
I mean, his car is here. The TV was on.

147
00:05:45,310 --> 00:05:47,300
His keys, his wallet, service revolver,

148
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:49,460
his phone, which I just started going through.

149
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:50,880
Password was his badge number

150
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:52,540
'cause who would've thought of that?

151
00:05:52,540 --> 00:05:53,700
Okay. Anything jump out?

152
00:05:53,700 --> 00:05:55,370
No, it's all just normal stuff.

153
00:05:55,380 --> 00:05:58,230
I mean, here I am texting him about the retirement party.

154
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:03,790
What?

155
00:06:04,510 --> 00:06:05,420
Talk to me.

156
00:06:10,540 --> 00:06:11,260
It says,

158
00:06:11,610 --> 00:06:13,390
Tuesday, 6:13,

159
00:06:13,820 --> 00:06:15,360
"You don't deliver, it's over."

160
00:06:15,510 --> 00:06:16,720
It's a restricted number.

161
00:06:18,430 --> 00:06:20,300
All right, any idea who might send something like that

162
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:21,360
to your old man?

163
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:22,360
No.

164
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:24,930
Tech said that the footprints

165
00:06:24,930 --> 00:06:26,800
and the blood leading to the back door

166
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:28,700
were made by somebody wearing socks.

167
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:31,550
So if this is what it seems, somebody grabbed him.

168
00:06:31,550 --> 00:06:33,470
Didn't even give him a chance to put his shoes on.

169
00:06:34,390 --> 00:06:36,130
All right. Keep canvassing this block.

170
00:06:36,130 --> 00:06:37,160
Find some cameras.

171
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:39,710
Scrape together enough to get a BOLO out on that car.

172
00:06:39,710 --> 00:06:40,930
- Kim. - Yeah.

173
00:06:41,790 --> 00:06:44,070
I want a full scrub of all of Bob Ruzek's cases,

174
00:06:44,070 --> 00:06:44,870
top to bottom.

175
00:06:44,870 --> 00:06:46,300
Something like this happened to one of us,

176
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:48,800
the first thing we'd think it's related to a case somehow.

177
00:06:48,810 --> 00:06:49,530
- Right. - Revenge,

178
00:06:49,530 --> 00:06:51,370
- somebody seeking information-- - Boss.

179
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:55,030
My pop spent the last 20 years directing traffic

180
00:06:55,030 --> 00:06:57,080
at afternoon Sox games, not kicking in doors.

181
00:06:57,080 --> 00:06:59,500
I mean, I don't think Kim's gonna find anything there.

182
00:07:00,170 --> 00:07:02,060
Okay, he's still a police officer.

183
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:05,360
That man spent a lot of time on a lot of streets.

184
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:08,310
Do the work.

185
00:07:08,310 --> 00:07:09,360
Now, I'm on it.

186
00:07:18,610 --> 00:07:20,230
- Can I help you? - Gonna see Benny.

187
00:07:20,230 --> 00:07:21,750
Hey. You can't go back there.

189
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:25,180
No. Nope.

190
00:07:25,740 --> 00:07:27,270
- Nope. - Benny.

191
00:07:27,870 --> 00:07:28,550
Adam.

192
00:07:28,550 --> 00:07:31,040
Benny, we need to talk.

193
00:07:32,210 --> 00:07:33,280
Everybody, out.

194
00:07:43,290 --> 00:07:44,470
Adam, the hell is this?

195
00:07:44,470 --> 00:07:45,920
There's no Adam here, Benny.

196
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:47,420
Not tonight.

197
00:07:47,420 --> 00:07:49,230
There's just a cop up your ass.

198
00:07:50,290 --> 00:07:52,140
- Where's my father, Benny? - What?

199
00:07:52,270 --> 00:07:54,420
I know you texted him, told him to deliver.

200
00:07:54,420 --> 00:07:55,480
- I didn't-- - Where is he, Benny?

201
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:57,290
- That wasn't me; I swear. - No, no, no, where is he?

202
00:07:57,300 --> 00:07:58,910
- I--I don't-- - Benny.

203
00:07:59,030 --> 00:07:59,910
Hey, hey. Did you hurt my dad?

204
00:07:59,910 --> 00:08:01,100
No, no. I did not.

205
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:03,500
- Did you hurt my dad? - No, I did not.

206
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:04,820
Listen to me.

207
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:07,880
Now you just take a breath.

208
00:08:07,980 --> 00:08:09,960
I will tell you exactly what happened,

209
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:12,420
and you are not gonna do anything bananas.

210
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:13,270
Deal?

211
00:08:18,270 --> 00:08:19,450
Tell me what happened.

212
00:08:19,710 --> 00:08:23,470
Your pops-- I am not gonna lie--was in trouble with me.

213
00:08:23,580 --> 00:08:24,580
- Bad. - How bad?

214
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:26,070
Like real bad.

215
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:28,380
Truth is, you know it. I know it.

216
00:08:28,380 --> 00:08:30,440
He's the worst gambler I ever knew.

217
00:08:31,960 --> 00:08:33,950
Got into a hole and just kept digging deeper

218
00:08:33,950 --> 00:08:35,060
until I finally cut him off.

219
00:08:35,060 --> 00:08:36,220
Benny, just tell me how much.

220
00:08:36,220 --> 00:08:37,600
80 grand.

221
00:08:38,130 --> 00:08:39,490
80 grand?

222
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:43,160
Benny, how could you let it get that bad this time?

223
00:08:43,160 --> 00:08:44,720
- I mean, if you said hey, I-- - Listen to me.

224
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:47,410
I did not lay a finger on your father.

225
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:49,550
And the reason is simple.

226
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:51,840
He paid. All of it.

227
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:52,660
What are you talking about?

228
00:08:52,660 --> 00:08:54,300
- In cash. - No.

229
00:08:54,310 --> 00:08:55,540
Walked in one night, dropped it,

230
00:08:55,540 --> 00:08:57,140
walked out, I ain't seen him since.

231
00:08:57,140 --> 00:08:59,310
- Yeah? When's this? - About a month ago.

232
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:01,970
Date's in the ledger book if you need it.

233
00:09:05,390 --> 00:09:06,420
Sorry, Benny.

234
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:16,350
What, are you following me?

235
00:09:16,350 --> 00:09:17,900
Yes. Yes.

236
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:20,890
Look, you were clearly lying to Voight

237
00:09:20,890 --> 00:09:23,250
when you saw that text at your dad's house.

238
00:09:23,250 --> 00:09:23,760
I wanted to make sure

239
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:25,560
you weren't doing something extracurricular,

240
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:28,500
just plain ol' stupid. Were you?

241
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:29,850
Yeah. That'd be fair to say.

242
00:09:29,850 --> 00:09:30,650
And?

243
00:09:30,860 --> 00:09:33,550
And, well, it turns out a few weeks ago,

244
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:35,170
my father paid down an 80 grand debt.

245
00:09:35,170 --> 00:09:36,460
A few hours ago, he couldn't put down

246
00:09:36,460 --> 00:09:38,520
a $200 deposit on a bar.

247
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:40,990
And now he's gone.

248
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:42,970
Okay. Okay.

249
00:09:42,970 --> 00:09:44,190
You know how he got the 80 grand?

250
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,470
No, I don't.

251
00:09:45,860 --> 00:09:46,840
I thought I knew what was going on.

252
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:47,730
I don't.

253
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:52,170
Hey. We're gonna figure it out.

254
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:53,310
Yeah.

255
00:09:56,790 --> 00:09:58,400
It's the same restricted number.

256
00:10:00,450 --> 00:10:01,450
It's a video.

257
00:10:04,150 --> 00:10:05,340
- Hello, son. - Oh, my God.

258
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:06,790
I'm okay. I'm all right.

259
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:09,900
I just, um-- I'm in a bit of trouble here.

260
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:13,030
These guys--Los Tiranos--

261
00:10:13,420 --> 00:10:15,160
I don't need to tell you who they are.

262
00:10:16,530 --> 00:10:17,700
They got a problem.

263
00:10:19,140 --> 00:10:20,020
A snitch.

264
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:22,480
Someone on the inside

265
00:10:23,090 --> 00:10:24,660
that's giving them trouble.

266
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:27,850
So they need you-- I need you--

267
00:10:28,980 --> 00:10:30,360
to find out who it is.

268
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:33,960
And then give them the name, okay?

269
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:36,350
Or I'm gone for good, son. I'm gone.

270
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:38,710
We'll be back in touch.

271
00:10:43,750 --> 00:10:45,930
We got a Chicago cop missing 12 hours.

272
00:10:45,930 --> 00:10:47,380
Tell me something good.

273
00:10:47,690 --> 00:10:48,810
We looped in OCD?

274
00:10:48,810 --> 00:10:50,610
We got trap-and-trace on Officer's Ruzek's phone,

275
00:10:50,610 --> 00:10:51,490
but so far, nothing.

276
00:10:51,490 --> 00:10:54,070
Okay. What's the latest on the scrub of his police work?

277
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:54,840
I'm into it, Sarge.

278
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,870
It's just not a lot of meat on the bone.

279
00:10:56,870 --> 00:10:59,800
Okay, so, Sarge, this is the claim territory of Los Tiranos,

280
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:02,440
the Hispanic gang that's holding down Bob Ruzek.

281
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:03,740
So these guys are an umbrella gang,

282
00:11:03,740 --> 00:11:04,990
- cartel-connected. - Okay.

283
00:11:04,990 --> 00:11:06,390
They got hundreds of foot soldiers,

