00:23:22,750 --> 00:23:23,610
Stop!

554
00:23:25,480 --> 00:23:26,870
All right, all right. Move with me.

555
00:23:26,870 --> 00:23:28,210
Let's go wide. Go wide.

556
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:31,780
We got motion right here.

557
00:23:33,150 --> 00:23:34,930
Chicago PD! Barela, stop!

558
00:23:34,930 --> 00:23:35,810
- Out of the way! - Come on, move.

559
00:23:35,810 --> 00:23:36,670
- Out of the way! - Stop!

560
00:23:36,670 --> 00:23:38,280
- Come on, keep it moving. - Get out of the car.

561
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:40,060
Get out of here. Get out the way!

562
00:23:40,070 --> 00:23:42,230
Move. Help her!

563
00:23:42,230 --> 00:23:43,550
Help her! Help her!

564
00:23:43,630 --> 00:23:46,760
Barela going down 19th in a civilian vehicle!

565
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:57,670
- Hey, Joy. - Adam, hey.

566
00:23:57,670 --> 00:23:58,570
How's he doing?

567
00:23:58,610 --> 00:24:01,020
Two broken ribs, some hypothermia.

568
00:24:01,020 --> 00:24:03,130
He went through hell, but he'll be fine.

569
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:05,060
All right. That's good.

570
00:24:05,060 --> 00:24:06,740
He okay to put on some real clothes?

571
00:24:07,230 --> 00:24:09,130
Mm, close enough. He'll be out of here soon.

572
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:11,430
Thank you, Joy.

573
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:12,850
Officer.

574
00:24:14,570 --> 00:24:15,380
Pa.

575
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:16,990
Ah, there he is.

576
00:24:18,250 --> 00:24:19,180
Thanks, son.

577
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:25,120
All right, Pops.

578
00:24:26,110 --> 00:24:27,110
Truth time.

579
00:24:29,170 --> 00:24:31,770
You gotta tell me everything so we can find Lucas Barela.

580
00:24:31,770 --> 00:24:33,080
Oh, the guy who took me?

581
00:24:33,120 --> 00:24:33,980
Yeah.

582
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:36,810
Lu--Lucas? Wh--

583
00:24:36,930 --> 00:24:38,860
- What'd you say? Barela? - Stop what you're doing.

584
00:24:40,230 --> 00:24:42,120
You know exactly who he is.

585
00:24:42,220 --> 00:24:44,230
You arrested him 25 years ago.

586
00:24:44,230 --> 00:24:46,350
He got a reduced sentence in exchange for information.

587
00:24:46,350 --> 00:24:47,440
He worked for you.

588
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:51,040
So you know exactly who Lucas Barela is, Dad.

589
00:24:53,050 --> 00:24:54,160
Talk to me.

590
00:24:58,100 --> 00:24:59,440
You're good, kid.

591
00:25:03,750 --> 00:25:05,730
Back then, I was the guy in charge.

592
00:25:07,160 --> 00:25:08,970
Barela was a street rat.

593
00:25:09,790 --> 00:25:13,160
And over the years, you know, things changed.

594
00:25:13,160 --> 00:25:14,280
I stayed right where I was,

595
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:18,170
but Barela, he climbed to the top.

596
00:25:18,380 --> 00:25:20,880
And that's how paid off your debt with Benny.

597
00:25:20,890 --> 00:25:23,220
You went to Barela, right?

598
00:25:24,570 --> 00:25:25,620
Yeah.

599
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:29,050
- 10% a week. - Oh, my God.

600
00:25:30,730 --> 00:25:32,350
What the hell is wrong with you?

601
00:25:32,440 --> 00:25:34,450
You couldn't pay that off in a million years.

602
00:25:34,450 --> 00:25:35,670
- What are you thinking? - I know.

603
00:25:35,670 --> 00:25:37,300
He knew--he knew when he gave me the loan.

604
00:25:37,300 --> 00:25:39,050
He knew when I couldn't pay him back,

605
00:25:39,830 --> 00:25:41,330
he had me over a barrel.

606
00:25:41,330 --> 00:25:42,550
He had a cop over a barrel.

607
00:25:42,550 --> 00:25:43,940
That's worth more than--

608
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:46,290
more than any money.

609
00:25:46,290 --> 00:25:48,300
So that's when he, uh--

610
00:25:48,300 --> 00:25:50,480
he demanded that I, um,

611
00:25:52,080 --> 00:25:54,180
find out the name of the snitch.

612
00:25:55,930 --> 00:25:58,520
- And I-- - Came up short. I know.

613
00:26:01,150 --> 00:26:02,320
So time was up.

614
00:26:04,050 --> 00:26:06,800
And, uh, Barela and his guy...

615
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,660
- Hector Santiago. - Yeah.

616
00:26:09,330 --> 00:26:10,940
They came to the house.

617
00:26:11,960 --> 00:26:12,950
I fought like hell.

618
00:26:12,950 --> 00:26:15,520
I probably hurt that Santiago pretty bad too,

619
00:26:15,530 --> 00:26:17,990
but I--I couldn't get to my piece.

620
00:26:18,500 --> 00:26:19,490
And...

621
00:26:21,530 --> 00:26:23,520
Barela put a gun to my head.

622
00:26:26,630 --> 00:26:27,580
Then--

623
00:26:28,220 --> 00:26:31,080
and then that was-- that was it for me. I...

624
00:26:33,990 --> 00:26:35,520
He was ready, and I...

625
00:26:38,250 --> 00:26:39,310
And what, Dad?

626
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:42,960
I wasn't.

627
00:26:46,940 --> 00:26:48,140
And I broke.

628
00:26:51,320 --> 00:26:53,240
I did the only thing I could think of

629
00:26:54,060 --> 00:26:56,750
to save my life-- I sold out my own son.

630
00:26:57,700 --> 00:27:01,150
I told him that you were a cop, that you were a real cop,

631
00:27:01,150 --> 00:27:02,860
that you were a better cop than I ever was,

632
00:27:02,860 --> 00:27:04,980
and that you could find the name of that snitch.

633
00:27:12,650 --> 00:27:14,460
I should've just taken the bullet.

634
00:27:32,100 --> 00:27:33,490
I need to find Barela.

635
00:27:33,950 --> 00:27:34,760
Now.

636
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:35,920
No.

637
00:27:36,550 --> 00:27:38,110
What, Dad? What? No.

638
00:27:38,110 --> 00:27:39,110
The man almost killed you.

639
00:27:39,110 --> 00:27:40,080
What the hell are you talking about?

640
00:27:40,080 --> 00:27:42,160
- You gotta let him walk. - I'm not letting him walk.

641
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:44,390
Why--why would you even say that, man?

642
00:27:44,390 --> 00:27:45,450
Adam,

643
00:27:45,910 --> 00:27:48,320
I've been borrowing money from him for years--

644
00:27:49,080 --> 00:27:50,240
drug money.

645
00:27:51,310 --> 00:27:54,120
And then trying to get the name of the informant?

646
00:27:54,130 --> 00:27:56,930
You bring Barela in, that all comes out.

647
00:27:56,930 --> 00:27:58,240
That's the end of me.

648
00:27:58,240 --> 00:28:01,040
They'll bring charges. That'll be the end of my pension.

649
00:28:01,980 --> 00:28:04,780
Our name will be destroyed.

650
00:28:15,820 --> 00:28:17,050
Our name.

651
00:28:33,120 --> 00:28:34,210
How is he?

652
00:28:34,380 --> 00:28:35,750
Yeah. He'll be fine.

653
00:28:35,750 --> 00:28:37,210
It's all right. Leave it open.

654
00:28:39,440 --> 00:28:40,730
Sarge, um,

655
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:45,220
you know, if we find Barela and we bring him in,

656
00:28:45,700 --> 00:28:47,540
what would really be gained by that?

657
00:28:50,520 --> 00:28:51,950
Is that a real question?

658
00:28:51,950 --> 00:28:53,150
It's just...

659
00:28:53,990 --> 00:28:55,660
All this crap comes out, it's ugly.

660
00:28:55,660 --> 00:28:57,240
My father's career, his pension.

661
00:28:57,240 --> 00:28:58,380
Adam.

662
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:01,700
You gotta stop covering for him.

663
00:29:02,170 --> 00:29:03,690
You gotta start taking care of you.

664
00:29:03,690 --> 00:29:04,800
I am.

665
00:29:05,120 --> 00:29:08,100
The name Ruzek's gonna stain this department,

666
00:29:08,100 --> 00:29:10,750
and I gotta lug that around long after my dad is gone.

667
00:29:11,110 --> 00:29:12,630
All the people that matter,

668
00:29:13,480 --> 00:29:15,050
they know who you are.

669
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:18,500
I'm asking.

670
00:29:21,780 --> 00:29:23,140
The answer's no.

671
00:29:25,130 --> 00:29:26,680
We've been down this road before

672
00:29:26,680 --> 00:29:27,790
with your old man, haven't we?

673
00:29:27,790 --> 00:29:29,660
- Done things we had to do. - Yeah, I know.

674
00:29:29,660 --> 00:29:32,240
And this is how he repays the favor?

675
00:29:33,140 --> 00:29:35,360
Gets in bed with a new drug dealer.

676
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:37,270
Now you want me to just walk away?

677
00:29:38,020 --> 00:29:40,400
We gave it a shot? We're moving on?

678
00:29:40,940 --> 00:29:42,570
Olinsky told me my dad and you had beef.

679
00:29:42,570 --> 00:29:44,670
He was a dog cop!

680
00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:55,690
You think I'm not hearing you because of some beef

681
00:29:55,700 --> 00:29:58,280
I had with your old man 20 years ago?

682
00:29:58,310 --> 00:29:59,420
No.

683
00:30:02,830 --> 00:30:03,610
Let me tell you something.

684
00:30:03,610 --> 00:30:05,190
You do this to a cop--

685
00:30:05,950 --> 00:30:09,050
put a gun to his head, pull him from his home--

686
00:30:09,760 --> 00:30:11,350
you're not doing that to Disco Bob;

687
00:30:11,350 --> 00:30:13,990
you're doing it to the Chicago Police.

688
00:30:14,230 --> 00:30:15,480
You understand?

689
00:30:19,960 --> 00:30:23,530
And we--we're gonna find Lucas Barela.

690
00:30:24,660 --> 00:30:26,800
You can participate or not.

691
00:30:27,810 --> 00:30:30,620
And I will be watching to see what you choose.

692
00:30:34,020 --> 00:30:36,140
All right. What did we hear from our CIs?

693
00:30:36,510 --> 00:30:37,750
Buttoned up pretty tight, Sarge.

694
00:30:37,750 --> 00:30:39,040
So we're nowhere.

695
00:30:39,200 --> 00:30:41,200
Okay. The vehicle Barela stole?

696
00:30:41,630 --> 00:30:43,660
Patrol found it. Torched.

697
00:30:43,670 --> 00:30:45,780
Right. Safehouses, stash houses.

698
00:30:45,790 --> 00:30:48,000
Barela's on the run. He's gotta be somewhere.

699
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:49,910
We've gone through every inch of intel.

700
00:30:49,910 --> 00:30:52,240
- So we're nowhere. - Maybe not, Sarge.

701
00:30:53,750 --> 00:30:55,090
This is the last piece from the scrub I did

702
00:30:55,090 --> 00:30:56,960
- on Bob Ruzek's activity. - Okay.

703
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:59,100
This is the data from the chip from his squad car.

704
00:30:59,100 --> 00:31:01,620
Now every single one of his patrol stops

705
00:31:01,620 --> 00:31:04,070
can be justified as an on-duty call--

706
00:31:04,120 --> 00:31:05,840
all except for this one.

707
00:31:05,840 --> 00:31:08,230
2451 South May. It's in Pilsen.

708
00:31:08,230 --> 00:31:10,550
- In the heart of Los Tiranos. - Exactly.

709
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:13,010
Bob Ruzek stopped there five times.

710
00:31:13,030 --> 00:31:15,300
Never called it in. Always off the books.

711
00:31:15,300 --> 00:31:17,290
Hold on, you guys. 2451 South May.

712
00:31:17,290 --> 00:31:21,050
We've got Barela in that stolen civilian car on a traffic cam,

713
00:31:21,050 --> 00:31:24,860
and he was a block away from there headed in that direction.

714
00:31:26,010 --> 00:31:27,200
Let's move.

715
00:31:34,690 --> 00:31:37,400
The cases we bent the rules on over the years.

716
00:31:37,510 --> 00:31:39,020
The crooks we sent into the wind

717
00:31:39,030 --> 00:31:41,180
because bringing 'em in was more trouble than it was worth,

718
00:31:41,180 --> 00:31:43,570
but this one, we cling to like a dog on a bone.

719
00:31:44,730 --> 00:31:47,470
The name Ruzek's gonna be a joke from here on out.

720
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:51,630
My dad's a jackass, but he's right about one thing.

721
00:31:52,610 --> 00:31:55,240
Everybody'd be better off if Lucas Barela just...

722
00:31:56,360 --> 00:31:57,570
went away.

723
00:32:04,750 --> 00:32:05,990
We're four minutes out.

724
00:32:06,280 --> 00:32:09,480
Move on the house but quiet till we're all there.

725
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:11,230
All right. Here we go.

726
00:32:13,570 --> 00:32:14,740
On scene.

727
00:32:33,110 --> 00:32:34,630
- I'll take the back. - Wait.

728
00:32:53,830 --> 00:32:54,770
Hey. Back inside.

729
00:32:54,770 --> 00:32:56,030
Get back inside now.

730
00:33:05,010 --> 00:33:06,150
Adam!

731
00:33:13,370 --> 00:33:14,540
Adam!

732
00:33:15,340 --> 00:33:16,540
Adam!

733
00:33:27,820 --> 00:33:29,120
What did you do?

734
00:33:36,280 --> 00:33:37,310
5021I
5021 Ida.

735
00:33:37,310 --> 00:33:39,820
Shots fired by the police. One offender down.

736
00:33:40,430 --> 00:33:42,490
Roll the crime lab to our location.

737
00:33:43,930 --> 00:33:45,060
Copy.

738
00:33:53,810 --> 00:33:55,430
Street Deputy and IRT are on their way

739
00:33:55,430 --> 00:33:56,830
to open the investigation.

740
00:33:56,840 --> 00:33:58,080
All right. Good.

741
00:33:59,940 --> 00:34:01,170
You wanna talk it through?

742
00:34:01,550 --> 00:34:02,660
Yeah, sure.

743
00:34:02,710 --> 00:34:03,780
Went to apprehend Barela.

744
00:34:03,780 --> 00:34:05,970
He reached for his piece, so I put him down.

745
00:34:05,990 --> 00:34:08,010
Shot three times, hit him three times.

746
00:34:08,770 --> 00:34:10,170
Twice in the back.

747
00:34:10,450 --> 00:34:12,000
It was a good shoot, boss.

748
00:34:32,330 --> 00:34:34,480
IRT and COPA want to talk to me

749
00:34:34,740 --> 00:34:36,160
about your state of mind.

750
00:34:36,780 --> 00:34:38,110
I know I didn't see the shooting,

751
00:34:38,120 --> 00:34:39,340
but they want my version.

752
00:34:39,340 --> 00:34:40,680
Well, you didn't see it.

753
00:34:40,820 --> 00:34:42,310
So what is there to say?

754
00:34:43,120 --> 00:34:44,200
Right.

755
00:34:45,290 --> 00:34:47,070
- It was a good shoot. - I hope so.

756
00:34:47,080 --> 00:34:48,780
Yeah. What does that mean?

757
00:34:50,350 --> 00:34:52,750
It means that I'm worried about you, okay?

758
00:34:52,750 --> 00:34:53,690
I'm worried.

759
00:34:53,690 --> 00:34:54,410
I have seen you going

760
00:34:54,410 --> 00:34:55,860
through some stuff lately, and now this--

761
00:34:55,860 --> 00:34:58,160
Kim, stop dancing around with me.

762
00:34:59,550 --> 00:35:01,410
Say to me what you're really thinking.

763
00:35:03,930 --> 00:35:05,230
Say it.

764
00:35:17,040 --> 00:35:18,710
They got a video of the shoot.

765
00:35:22,940 --> 00:35:24,980
Security camera, house next door.

766
00:35:26,560 --> 00:35:27,580
Play it.

767
00:35:35,720 --> 00:35:37,050
What's he saying to you?

768
00:35:37,120 --> 00:35:38,950
He told me he knew who I was.

769
00:35:39,010 --> 00:35:39,800
I wouldn't bring him in

770
00:35:39,800 --> 00:35:42,830
because my father already promised to let him go,

771
00:35:42,830 --> 00:35:44,680
and he'd ruin my father's career.

772
00:35:45,220 --> 00:35:47,410
And that I was a little bitch like my old man.

773
00:35:51,150 --> 00:35:53,090
I told him he was wrong.

774
00:35:55,020 --> 00:35:56,000
He reached for his gun.

775
00:35:56,010 --> 00:35:58,620
He was moving fast, and the first shot spun him around.

776
00:35:58,700 --> 00:36:01,040
Second and third shots went through his back.

777
00:36:06,670 --> 00:36:07,950
Good shoot.

778
00:36:09,450 --> 00:36:11,270
That went down exactly like you said,

779
00:36:11,280 --> 00:36:13,840
exactly as you reported to IRT.

780
00:36:15,240 --> 00:36:16,620
- That's good work, Ruzek. - Thanks.

781
00:36:16,620 --> 00:36:18,130
- Nice shoot. - Thanks.

782
00:36:32,830 --> 00:36:34,360
Hey, Adam. How is he?

783
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:36,240
Oh, yeah. He's gonna be fine, Sarge.

784
00:36:36,240 --> 00:36:38,530
He got out of the hospital yesterday, so.

785
00:36:38,530 --> 00:36:40,200
- Thanks for asking, Sarge. - Yeah.

786
00:36:44,380 --> 00:36:46,080
Hey, you know that stuff you said

787
00:36:46,340 --> 00:36:48,330
about my old man coming into shift talking

788
00:36:48,330 --> 00:36:49,570
about my little league games?

789
00:36:49,580 --> 00:36:50,720
Yeah?

790
00:36:51,560 --> 00:36:52,910
Total BS.

791
00:36:53,270 --> 00:36:54,240
What?

792
00:36:54,240 --> 00:36:55,350
Yeah. He made it up.

793
00:36:55,350 --> 00:36:57,010
That was his shtick.

794
00:36:57,120 --> 00:36:58,030
Couldn't be the real police.

795
00:36:58,030 --> 00:36:59,320
Couldn't be the first guy through the door

796
00:36:59,320 --> 00:37:00,990
because he was a family man.

797
00:37:01,640 --> 00:37:03,940
Even if it hurt his career, he had to be home for dinner

798
00:37:03,940 --> 00:37:06,120
and in the stands for my games.

799
00:37:07,270 --> 00:37:08,540
He made it all up.

800
00:37:09,110 --> 00:37:10,980
He was at the bar making bad bets.

801
00:37:13,900 --> 00:37:15,730
I knew you weren't that good a hitter.

802
00:37:16,950 --> 00:37:18,150
- Thanks, Sarge. - Yep.

803
00:37:18,150 --> 00:37:20,070
Taking that over to the Deputy Supe?

804
00:37:20,690 --> 00:37:22,870
Yeah, you know. Case like this, I gotta.

805
00:37:22,870 --> 00:37:24,060
Yeah.

806
00:37:24,200 --> 00:37:25,800
All it says is the truth.

807
00:37:26,520 --> 00:37:28,500
Officer Ruzek was abducted

808
00:37:28,500 --> 00:37:30,190
because the offender was under the mistaken belief

809
00:37:30,200 --> 00:37:32,030
he knew the identity of a CI.

810
00:37:33,010 --> 00:37:34,290
Anything else,

811
00:37:34,960 --> 00:37:37,080
that'll die with Lucas Barela.

812
00:37:37,090 --> 00:37:38,230
Boss.

813
00:37:40,620 --> 00:37:41,970
I don't know what to say.

814
00:37:44,220 --> 00:37:46,510
That's the best news I've had all day.

815
00:37:59,190 --> 00:38:01,140
You must be damn proud, Adam.

816
00:38:01,490 --> 00:38:03,360
Hell of a legacy to carry on.

817
00:38:04,950 --> 00:38:06,230
Sure is.

818
00:38:16,410 --> 00:38:17,500
Thanks, Duff.

819
00:38:52,130 --> 00:38:53,500
We need to clear the air.

820
00:38:54,830 --> 00:38:55,900
All right.

821
00:38:56,140 --> 00:38:57,970
- Adam-- - When you ran up on me

822
00:38:58,420 --> 00:38:59,980
after I shot Barela,

823
00:39:01,370 --> 00:39:04,380
you could've asked me if I was okay,

824
00:39:04,380 --> 00:39:05,950
if I was hurt-- that's not what you did.

825
00:39:05,950 --> 00:39:07,760
- Adam, listen. - You said, "What did you do?"

826
00:39:07,860 --> 00:39:08,960
Yeah, I did.

827
00:39:10,260 --> 00:39:11,650
"What did you do?"

828
00:39:14,630 --> 00:39:15,700
Kim,

829
00:39:17,230 --> 00:39:20,120
one of the many reasons that I fell in love with you

830
00:39:20,120 --> 00:39:23,260
is that I felt like you believed in me.

831
00:39:23,490 --> 00:39:24,480
Like you believed in me

832
00:39:24,490 --> 00:39:28,410
in a way that nobody in my entire life has.

833
00:39:28,410 --> 00:39:29,010
I did.

834
00:39:29,010 --> 00:39:30,450
- Even me. - I do.

835
00:39:30,450 --> 00:39:31,910
I'm not so sure.

836
00:39:34,480 --> 00:39:37,190
You have to see how what I said made sense in the moment.

837
00:39:37,980 --> 00:39:39,370
You have to see that.

838
00:39:39,650 --> 00:39:40,770
I don't.

839
00:39:42,310 --> 00:39:44,670
After everything that you and I have been through,

840
00:39:45,970 --> 00:39:47,880
there just should have been something that...

841
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:51,140
Held you back from the edge of assumption.

842
00:39:51,140 --> 00:39:52,950
Some sort of guardrail

843
00:39:52,950 --> 00:39:54,700
that kept you from going over that ledge.

844
00:39:54,710 --> 00:39:57,150
I mean, if this situation is reversed--

845
00:39:57,230 --> 00:39:58,610
I'm you; you're me--

846
00:39:58,860 --> 00:39:59,930
and I run up on you.

847
00:39:59,930 --> 00:40:01,620
You're standing over Barela holding the gun.

848
00:40:01,620 --> 00:40:04,880
If I got close to the ledge, fine--I wouldn't go over.

849
00:40:05,810 --> 00:40:07,010
Not ever.

850
00:40:09,500 --> 00:40:10,550
I just...

851
00:40:14,390 --> 00:40:15,950
'Cause I know your heart.

852
00:40:17,060 --> 00:40:19,490
And I know that there's not a world in which

853
00:40:19,730 --> 00:40:21,290
you'd kill a man in cold blood,

854
00:40:21,290 --> 00:40:23,500
that you'd shoot him in the back as he's running away.

855
00:40:23,500 --> 00:40:25,630
For what--revenge? For your family name?

856
00:40:25,630 --> 00:40:26,780
Come on.

857
00:40:27,080 --> 00:40:28,480
That's what you meant

858
00:40:29,520 --> 00:40:31,220
when you said, "What did you do?"

859
00:40:32,450 --> 00:40:33,890
And in that moment,

860
00:40:35,050 --> 00:40:37,020
I'd have thought you'd know my heart.

861
00:40:38,600 --> 00:40:40,050
You're supposed to know.

862
00:40:42,970 --> 00:40:44,590
I do know your heart. I do.

863
00:40:44,600 --> 00:40:45,970
And I am sorry.

864
00:40:46,230 --> 00:40:47,500
- Just-- - I--

865
00:40:48,440 --> 00:40:50,060
Thanks for stopping by.

